1
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:17,410
(Come in at the office today
to talk about the fan meeting, Kaye.)

2
00:02:15,158 --> 00:02:16,598
And remember…

3
00:02:16,659 --> 00:02:20,398
It has to be fun, exciting,
but heartwarming.

4
00:02:20,597 --> 00:02:21,208
You copy?

5
00:02:21,254 --> 00:02:22,902
That’s your homework for the day.

6
00:02:23,154 --> 00:02:25,976
Oh, there he is!

7
00:02:26,005 --> 00:02:28,099
Our main character.

8
00:02:30,819 --> 00:02:33,050
Listen. I’ve got good news.

9
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:37,920
The pre-order for your new comic
just hit the target!

10
00:02:38,005 --> 00:02:38,903
Well done!

11
00:02:40,684 --> 00:02:41,650
Well done!

12
00:02:44,124 --> 00:02:46,702
And… my commission?

13
00:02:46,930 --> 00:02:48,998
Come on. I won’t forget that.

14
00:02:49,296 --> 00:02:51,884
Don’t forget either
that you wouldn’t be here today

15
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:53,080
if I didn’t give you a chance.

16
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,702
Fame is more important than money.

17
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:56,702
You hear me?

18
00:02:57,745 --> 00:02:58,863
Look.

19
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:03,010
You gotta smile more.

20
00:03:03,288 --> 00:03:05,100
Sign your autograph.

21
00:03:05,389 --> 00:03:07,099
I guarantee you’ll be rich.

22
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:08,299
Alright?

23
00:03:12,856 --> 00:03:14,497
Why’d you let it slide?

24
00:03:15,340 --> 00:03:16,598
You’re gonna miss it.

25
00:03:17,423 --> 00:03:21,102
(Following the mysterious disappearance
of Mr. Krekpol Thanupaisarn,)

26
00:03:21,131 --> 00:03:22,900
(the CEO of KT Group,)

27
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:25,897
(police are currently investigating)

28
00:03:25,930 --> 00:03:28,315
(and questioning
his close friends and family.)

29
00:03:29,168 --> 00:03:31,450
Krekpol never disappeared like this.

30
00:03:31,693 --> 00:03:34,242
He always lets me know where he’s going.

31
00:03:34,275 --> 00:03:36,696
But it’s been four days.

32
00:03:36,783 --> 00:03:38,699
Who knows what’s going on with him?

33
00:03:38,897 --> 00:03:40,598
Who was the last person who saw him?

34
00:03:49,407 --> 00:03:50,297
The maid.

35
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:55,610
She said she saw him in his office
late at night on Friday.

36
00:03:56,296 --> 00:03:58,997
But he was gone by the morning.

37
00:04:00,453 --> 00:04:01,697
His car is still here,

38
00:04:02,459 --> 00:04:04,130
as well as his phone.

39
00:04:05,111 --> 00:04:06,601
No sign of forced entry.

40
00:04:07,348 --> 00:04:09,410
The security guard said
there were no visitors.

41
00:04:14,340 --> 00:04:15,302
Please, officer.

42
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:45,604
No sign of struggle.

43
00:04:47,038 --> 00:04:49,200
The victim is a middle aged man
with a stout figure.

44
00:04:49,650 --> 00:04:53,100
If he resisted, it should have
made a mess of this room.

45
00:04:53,614 --> 00:04:56,897
Maybe the victim knows his kidnapper?

46
00:04:57,742 --> 00:04:58,900
Maybe…

47
00:04:59,802 --> 00:05:01,699
The kidnapper had the upper hand,

48
00:05:02,798 --> 00:05:04,297
such as pointing a gun at the vic,

49
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:05,497
or poisoning him.

50
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,650
BEST CO-FOUNDER AWARD
THAI INVESTMENT BANK, 2003

51
00:05:24,610 --> 00:05:25,902
Antihypertensive.

52
00:05:26,588 --> 00:05:27,980
Heart disease medication.

53
00:05:34,610 --> 00:05:36,099
From the evidence,

54
00:05:36,522 --> 00:05:39,985
we can conclude
that the victim was forced to disappear.

55
00:05:42,604 --> 00:05:44,699
In most ransom cases,

56
00:05:45,192 --> 00:05:47,370
the kidnapper makes contact
within the first two days.

57
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:50,401
But it’s been dead silent.

58
00:05:52,346 --> 00:05:53,500
…Which means?

59
00:05:54,730 --> 00:05:57,900
Which means the kidnapper
doesn’t want money,

60
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,398
they just want to take him

61
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:02,699
or…

62
00:06:04,122 --> 00:06:04,896
His life.

63
00:06:06,997 --> 00:06:07,801
Inspector.

64
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,697
We found Krekpol.

65
00:08:01,026 --> 00:08:02,690
Is this some kind of Satanism?

66
00:08:04,580 --> 00:08:05,400
Listen up.

67
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,300
Secure every bit of evidence.

68
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,499
The murderer didn’t just want to kill him,

69
00:08:09,958 --> 00:08:11,297
they wanted to send a message.

70
00:08:12,817 --> 00:08:14,400
I don’t believe there’s only one body.

71
00:08:14,950 --> 00:08:16,500
Sieve through missing person cases.

72
00:08:17,112 --> 00:08:19,896
Report back to me
when you find anything suspicious.

73
00:08:20,940 --> 00:08:21,645
Yes, sir.

74
00:12:08,687 --> 00:12:09,496
Kaye.

75
00:12:10,037 --> 00:12:12,000
What happened to your arm?
It’s black and blue.

76
00:12:13,180 --> 00:12:13,896
Oh.

77
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,296
It’s nothing.

78
00:12:15,826 --> 00:12:18,201
I slipped and fell in the bathroom
this morning.

79
00:12:18,429 --> 00:12:20,600
I guess it left a little bruise.

80
00:12:21,010 --> 00:12:23,102
I don’t think it’s little
by the look of it.

81
00:12:24,379 --> 00:12:26,296
You gotta take better care of yourself,
you know?

82
00:12:26,325 --> 00:12:27,899
You’re as thin as a rake.

83
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:31,800
You need to be persistent
about your commission, you know?

84
00:12:31,850 --> 00:12:33,099
Dude’s gonna pretend he forgets.

85
00:12:34,770 --> 00:12:35,595
Of course.

86
00:12:35,857 --> 00:12:37,800
Oh, look at that smile.

87
00:12:38,435 --> 00:12:40,195
You’re too adorable when you smile, dude.

88
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:41,974
He ain’t gonna be scared
when you make a demand.

89
00:12:42,001 --> 00:12:43,200
Be more firm!

90
00:12:43,225 --> 00:12:44,702
Ask for your money firmly, you hear me?

91
00:12:52,811 --> 00:12:55,297
Let’s get back to our beloved job,
shall we?

92
00:12:59,589 --> 00:13:00,699
All good?

93
00:13:09,571 --> 00:13:10,330
What?

94
00:13:11,802 --> 00:13:13,450
You brought a hammer to work?

95
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:16,601
Did you plan to smash our editor’s head?

96
00:13:19,438 --> 00:13:20,737
Oh, no.

97
00:13:20,761 --> 00:13:24,121
I was fixing my chair at home yesterday.

98
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:26,804
It must have slipped into my bag.

99
00:13:28,951 --> 00:13:30,302
It’s a hammer, not an inhaler.

100
00:13:30,539 --> 00:13:32,602
It doesn’t just slip into your bag, man.

101
00:13:35,860 --> 00:13:36,795
But that’s alright.

102
00:13:37,669 --> 00:13:38,600
I’m borrowing it.

103
00:13:38,974 --> 00:13:41,800
There’s a nail sticking out under my desk.

104
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,977
It tore two of my favorite pants, actually.

105
00:13:44,370 --> 00:13:45,601
These are new.

106
00:13:45,662 --> 00:13:46,127
Sure.

107
00:13:46,155 --> 00:13:47,610
Thanks, bro.

108
00:13:54,017 --> 00:13:55,352
Nice weight!

109
00:13:57,710 --> 00:13:58,998
I’m just gonna take a minute.

110
00:14:05,650 --> 00:14:08,558
(Yesterday at 5 p.m.,)

111
00:14:08,579 --> 00:14:14,300
(police found the body of a man
in an abandoned warehouse in Bangna.)

112
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:18,974
(Initial report identifies him
as Mr. Krekpol Thanupaisarn, 52 years old,)

113
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,071
(the CEO of KT Group.)

114
00:14:21,090 --> 00:14:24,530
(The police are working
to gather the evidence right now,)

115
00:14:24,909 --> 00:14:27,761
(as well as checking all security cameras
around the area)

116
00:14:27,786 --> 00:14:30,195
(and questioning everyone involved.)

117
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:32,600
Oh, they found the body.

118
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:33,798
So he’s dead?

119
00:14:34,149 --> 00:14:36,161
Isn’t this the man
who swindled his company

120
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:39,048
and laid off 40,000 people?

121
00:14:39,099 --> 00:14:40,097
Yeah.

122
00:14:43,802 --> 00:14:45,302
Karma works fast.

123
00:14:47,045 --> 00:14:48,161
And he definitely paid for it.

124
00:15:05,140 --> 00:15:08,170
His time of death
was between 24-30 hours ago.

125
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:11,499
Which means the victim was held captive
three days before he was murdered.

126
00:15:12,894 --> 00:15:14,496
Why three days?

127
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:17,497
Was it out of guilt?

128
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:20,997
Or were they waiting for something?

129
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:31,290
HAMMER

130
00:15:31,510 --> 00:15:33,998
None of the injuries were fatal.

131
00:15:34,946 --> 00:15:36,450
The murderer only meant to hurt,

132
00:15:36,625 --> 00:15:39,902
likely so the victim begged for his life
until his last breath.

133
00:15:44,628 --> 00:15:46,198
Hey, you’re back!

134
00:15:46,950 --> 00:15:47,748
Hello?

135
00:15:51,230 --> 00:15:52,235
Look at you.

136
00:15:52,265 --> 00:15:53,700
You look like a zombie.

137
00:15:53,845 --> 00:15:54,991
You need to sleep more.

138
00:15:55,010 --> 00:15:56,195
I got you some snacks.

139
00:15:59,610 --> 00:16:00,601
I’m working.

140
00:16:00,754 --> 00:16:02,290
I told you not to barge in.

141
00:16:02,597 --> 00:16:04,696
You probably didn’t hear it but I knocked.

142
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:07,398
Speaking of which, I need your help.

143
00:16:07,710 --> 00:16:08,497
What?

144
00:16:08,764 --> 00:16:09,973
You need money again?

145
00:16:10,112 --> 00:16:10,897
Nope.

146
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:14,702
I have to apply for an internship
at school tomorrow.

147
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:17,503
But there’s an important appointment
I can’t miss.

148
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:19,496
Appointment? With who?

149
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:22,998
Can you get his autograph for me?

150
00:16:25,687 --> 00:16:26,800
Romance manga?

151
00:16:26,933 --> 00:16:27,597
Yep.

152
00:16:28,195 --> 00:16:29,597
Nope. I’m not doing it.

153
00:16:30,512 --> 00:16:31,401
Please.

154
00:16:31,530 --> 00:16:33,850
I don’t know if I’ll ever get
another chance like this.

155
00:16:34,170 --> 00:16:35,334
If I’m in the interview,

156
00:16:35,351 --> 00:16:38,591
worrying about not getting
Kaye’s autograph, what will I do?

157
00:16:38,619 --> 00:16:40,402
You want me to miss my internship?

158
00:16:41,788 --> 00:16:42,900
Fine.

159
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:44,103
Okay.

160
00:16:44,789 --> 00:16:45,699
I’ll get it for you.

161
00:16:45,730 --> 00:16:46,500
You sure?

162
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:47,176
Yeah.

163
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:48,470
-Are you sure?
-I just said yes.

164
00:16:48,491 --> 00:16:49,850
-You mean it?
-I do.

165
00:16:50,965 --> 00:16:51,976
Give me a hug.

166
00:16:52,352 --> 00:16:53,398
My bro.

167
00:16:55,748 --> 00:16:56,699
But right now,

168
00:16:57,309 --> 00:16:58,404
you have to go.

169
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:00,597
I’m working and I need complete focus.

170
00:17:01,358 --> 00:17:02,297
Okay.

171
00:17:02,441 --> 00:17:02,973
Let me see.

172
00:17:03,026 --> 00:17:03,696
Hey.

173
00:17:04,339 --> 00:17:05,496
Go back to your room!

174
00:17:05,674 --> 00:17:07,004
-Go!
-I just need a peek.

175
00:17:07,094 --> 00:17:08,208
You’re a kid. You’re not allowed.

176
00:17:08,234 --> 00:17:08,900
Go.

177
00:17:39,743 --> 00:17:40,703
Look.

178
00:17:41,117 --> 00:17:42,610
You gotta smile more.

179
00:17:42,860 --> 00:17:44,601
Sign your autograph.

180
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:46,900
(I guarantee you’ll be rich.)

181
00:18:08,899 --> 00:18:10,702
Hello!

182
00:18:10,810 --> 00:18:13,730
Welcome to today’s event.

183
00:18:14,071 --> 00:18:18,400
This is your chance to meet
the famous comic author,

184
00:18:18,428 --> 00:18:21,682
whose anthology is coming out soon.

185
00:18:21,773 --> 00:18:24,680
I bet you can’t wait to meet him.

186
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:26,302
2500?

187
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:29,303
For a whole set and an autograph.

188
00:18:29,540 --> 00:18:32,121
At this point, I think everyone knows him…

189
00:18:32,302 --> 00:18:34,170
5500 for a VIP package?

190
00:18:35,590 --> 00:18:37,699
Does a twelfth grader
really need all this?

191
00:18:38,690 --> 00:18:42,900
Please welcome Mr. K.Cupid.

192
00:18:46,622 --> 00:18:48,022
Hello.

193
00:18:49,939 --> 00:18:51,100
Please have a seat.

194
00:18:56,838 --> 00:18:57,976
How are you feeling?

195
00:18:59,835 --> 00:19:00,582
Hello.

196
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,360
Can I have your name
and your ticket, please?

197
00:19:02,390 --> 00:19:04,060
Uh… I’m here in my sister’s place.

198
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:07,004
Then please show us your ID card.

199
00:19:07,414 --> 00:19:08,100
Okay.

200
00:19:16,100 --> 00:19:17,066
Alright.

201
00:19:17,318 --> 00:19:19,210
Miss Praew, VIP ticket.

202
00:19:26,985 --> 00:19:28,703
V–VIP?

203
00:19:28,847 --> 00:19:29,699
Yes, sir.

204
00:19:29,807 --> 00:19:31,798
VIP ticket holders will receive a T-shirt,

205
00:19:32,106 --> 00:19:36,176
the book, and autographed
exclusive posters for all three series,

206
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:37,890
and a photo session with the author.

207
00:19:38,376 --> 00:19:40,395
You will receive all of these on stage.

208
00:19:40,891 --> 00:19:43,899
Do I… have to take a photo with him?

209
00:19:43,982 --> 00:19:44,699
Yes.

210
00:19:44,878 --> 00:19:49,600
Will you pay for the ticket
with cash or by QR code?

211
00:19:50,595 --> 00:19:52,530
It’s not paid?

212
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:55,198
Only the deposit, sir.

213
00:20:02,266 --> 00:20:03,096
QR code?

214
00:20:03,234 --> 00:20:03,976
Yes.

215
00:20:10,853 --> 00:20:11,794
-All done?
-Here.

216
00:20:11,810 --> 00:20:12,250
Yes.

217
00:20:12,281 --> 00:20:13,180
Thank you.

218
00:20:17,540 --> 00:20:19,102
-How should I do it?
-Kitty kiss.

219
00:20:26,059 --> 00:20:26,957
Thank you.

220
00:20:27,084 --> 00:20:28,400
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

221
00:20:31,308 --> 00:20:32,204
Hello.

222
00:20:38,371 --> 00:20:39,697
What a hellish day.

223
00:20:40,980 --> 00:20:42,900
I should have made Win do this.

224
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:45,980
Thank you. Don’t forget to get
some souvenirs before you leave.

225
00:20:46,008 --> 00:20:47,000
Thank you.

226
00:20:56,731 --> 00:20:57,896
What do you think you’re doing?

227
00:20:58,297 --> 00:20:59,000
No.

228
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:00,640
I’m not doing anything.

229
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:02,250
I’m just taking some photos of Kaye.

230
00:21:03,077 --> 00:21:04,600
-Let go.
-Kaye, my foot.

231
00:21:04,681 --> 00:21:05,850
You held your phone too low.

232
00:21:07,231 --> 00:21:08,400
I didn’t do anything!

233
00:21:09,041 --> 00:21:09,850
Show me your phone.

234
00:21:10,423 --> 00:21:11,600
-Let go!
-Hey.

235
00:21:11,650 --> 00:21:12,502
I didn’t do anything wrong.

236
00:21:12,906 --> 00:21:13,848
Excuse me. Excuse me.

237
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:14,998
Please let go.

238
00:21:16,773 --> 00:21:17,697
Take it easy.

239
00:21:17,825 --> 00:21:18,699
What happened?

240
00:21:18,740 --> 00:21:20,130
Did you have to be so forceful with him?

241
00:21:22,597 --> 00:21:24,404
What happened?

242
00:21:24,650 --> 00:21:25,348
Nothing.

243
00:21:25,597 --> 00:21:26,496
I didn’t do anything.

244
00:21:26,810 --> 00:21:27,697
I didn’t do anything wrong.

245
00:21:27,990 --> 00:21:30,296
If you didn’t, show me your phone.

246
00:21:48,228 --> 00:21:48,899
Let go!

247
00:21:50,192 --> 00:21:50,737
Let go.

248
00:21:50,950 --> 00:21:51,500
Let go.

249
00:21:51,674 --> 00:21:52,234
Let go of me.

250
00:21:52,254 --> 00:21:53,623
I didn’t do anything wrong. Let go.

251
00:21:54,139 --> 00:21:55,000
Let go of me!

252
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:55,853
Let go.

253
00:21:55,988 --> 00:21:56,542
Let go.

254
00:21:56,570 --> 00:21:57,977
I didn’t do anything wrong! Let go!

255
00:21:59,080 --> 00:21:59,801
Let go.

256
00:22:00,281 --> 00:22:00,903
Let go!

257
00:22:01,645 --> 00:22:02,499
Let go of me!

258
00:22:11,404 --> 00:22:14,896
We’ll let you know
when everything’s sorted out.

259
00:22:14,925 --> 00:22:15,605
Thank you.

260
00:22:15,697 --> 00:22:16,405
Of course.

261
00:22:20,085 --> 00:22:21,804
I’m really sorry about earlier.

262
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:25,000
I thought you were attacking him.

263
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:26,696
I didn’t know he was a…

264
00:22:28,162 --> 00:22:29,102
Never mind that.

265
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:33,170
Perverts at crowded events like this
are more common than you think.

266
00:22:34,491 --> 00:22:35,198
Right.

267
00:22:36,601 --> 00:22:37,500
Excuse me.

268
00:22:38,940 --> 00:22:42,798
Would it be okay if I have a snapshot
of the famous author and our hero today?

269
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:45,306
Sure.

270
00:22:45,339 --> 00:22:46,197
Of course.

271
00:22:47,731 --> 00:22:48,600
Over here, please.

272
00:22:53,128 --> 00:22:54,198
Allow me.

273
00:22:54,782 --> 00:22:56,697
One, two…

274
00:22:57,480 --> 00:22:58,305
Alright.

275
00:22:59,647 --> 00:23:00,797
Can you get a little closer?

276
00:23:01,496 --> 00:23:02,601
That’s nice.

277
00:23:02,825 --> 00:23:03,500
Alright.

278
00:23:08,709 --> 00:23:10,700
I think that’s enough.

279
00:23:11,059 --> 00:23:12,597
The flash is hurting my eyes.

280
00:23:13,023 --> 00:23:14,900
Oh, right.

281
00:23:14,995 --> 00:23:15,936
Thank you.

282
00:23:15,962 --> 00:23:16,702
Sure.

283
00:23:22,094 --> 00:23:23,977
Uh, wait, wait.

284
00:23:24,054 --> 00:23:27,165
I want to thank you for earlier.

285
00:23:27,192 --> 00:23:29,696
If you weren’t there,
I might be in trouble.

286
00:23:30,085 --> 00:23:32,102
Can I do anything to thank you for that?

287
00:23:32,742 --> 00:23:34,697
That won’t be necessary.

288
00:23:35,533 --> 00:23:39,900
I’ll send you the photos from the event
when I have them.

289
00:23:40,278 --> 00:23:41,598
Oh, uh…

290
00:23:41,823 --> 00:23:42,490
Oh, I know.

291
00:23:42,635 --> 00:23:45,404
It’s… it’s alright.

292
00:23:45,910 --> 00:23:46,699
Here.

293
00:23:49,088 --> 00:23:50,600
What are you doing?

294
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:51,500
Hey.

295
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,499
Hey, what are you doing?

296
00:23:55,056 --> 00:23:56,700
My autograph.

297
00:23:57,420 --> 00:23:59,696
Please don’t tell anyone I did that.

298
00:23:59,790 --> 00:24:02,250
My editor will have my head
if he finds out.

299
00:24:02,671 --> 00:24:05,397
Autographs are lucrative these days,
I heard.

300
00:24:05,525 --> 00:24:07,521
You can let me know
which ship is your favorite.

301
00:24:07,542 --> 00:24:09,500
I’ll write it down, too.

302
00:24:10,370 --> 00:24:11,300
Oh, crap.

303
00:24:11,411 --> 00:24:12,497
You got it wrong.

304
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,834
I’m only here because my sister couldn’t.

305
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:17,302
Ugh!

306
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:19,001
-My jacket.
-Shit…

307
00:24:19,911 --> 00:24:22,097
I’m so sorry.

308
00:24:24,271 --> 00:24:25,028
I’m sorry.

309
00:24:25,069 --> 00:24:26,200
Forget it.

310
00:24:27,930 --> 00:24:30,598
It’s worth something, right?

311
00:24:31,091 --> 00:24:32,900
I’ll sell it to my sister.

312
00:24:33,761 --> 00:24:35,730
She tricked me into paying
for your fan meeting.

313
00:24:37,831 --> 00:24:38,801
Kaye.

314
00:24:39,333 --> 00:24:40,900
Please be on standby.

315
00:24:40,930 --> 00:24:42,299
The fans are waiting.

316
00:24:50,903 --> 00:24:52,302
This way, please.

317
00:25:18,481 --> 00:25:19,629
Hello, sir.

318
00:25:22,311 --> 00:25:23,296
Inspector.

319
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,502
Is that a celebrity’s autograph?

320
00:25:26,570 --> 00:25:27,934
Right on your back.

321
00:25:27,977 --> 00:25:29,669
That must be so damn exclusive.

322
00:25:31,546 --> 00:25:32,900
Any updates on the case?

323
00:25:35,848 --> 00:25:37,700
From the missing person files,

324
00:25:37,934 --> 00:25:39,490
this one stands out.

325
00:25:39,783 --> 00:25:41,497
Mr. Teerakorn Dechorattana,

326
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:43,143
the former permanent secretary
of the Ministry of Agriculture.

327
00:25:43,165 --> 00:25:44,672
He’s been reported missing
for 48 hours now.

328
00:25:44,694 --> 00:25:48,220
Witness pinpoints his last sighting
at his own home in Pathum Thani.

329
00:25:48,242 --> 00:25:50,099
His car was gone, too.

330
00:25:50,653 --> 00:25:51,977
48 hours?

331
00:25:52,783 --> 00:25:54,010
Kidnap and ransom?

332
00:25:54,308 --> 00:25:56,120
His position at work would make him
a lot of enemies.

333
00:25:56,143 --> 00:26:00,400
What’s with the pesticide policy
all those years ago.

334
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:01,700
No…

335
00:26:02,814 --> 00:26:04,204
48 hours.

336
00:26:05,525 --> 00:26:06,703
Missing.

337
00:26:07,377 --> 00:26:08,499
No contact.

338
00:26:08,871 --> 00:26:09,800
Radio silent.

339
00:26:11,134 --> 00:26:12,400
Just like the Krekpol case.

340
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:20,570
4 DAYS MISSING
1 DAY BEFORE MURDER
3 DAYS LOCKED UP

341
00:26:21,450 --> 00:26:23,400
Krekpol’s autopsy shows

342
00:26:23,820 --> 00:26:27,112
he was tortured for three days
before he was murdered.

343
00:26:27,429 --> 00:26:29,897
Teerakorn has been missing
for two days now.

344
00:26:30,802 --> 00:26:32,543
If this pattern sticks…

345
00:26:32,945 --> 00:26:34,402
Are you suggesting…

346
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:37,700
This is the work of a serial killer?

347
00:26:39,060 --> 00:26:41,120
I’m sure it is.

348
00:26:41,598 --> 00:26:42,497
Listen up.

349
00:26:43,248 --> 00:26:45,299
Based on Krekpol’s case,

350
00:26:45,630 --> 00:26:49,228
he was missing for three days
before he was murdered.

351
00:26:50,459 --> 00:26:53,416
Right now, Teerakorn has been missing
for two days.

352
00:26:54,179 --> 00:26:56,401
That means we have 24 hours…

353
00:26:58,010 --> 00:26:59,299
Or even less.

354
00:27:00,401 --> 00:27:01,300
Remember this.

355
00:27:02,444 --> 00:27:04,040
We’re not looking for a body.

356
00:27:04,510 --> 00:27:06,297
We’re looking for a man who’s still alive.

357
00:27:20,570 --> 00:27:21,602
Show me that one.

358
00:27:52,770 --> 00:27:53,565
Yes?

359
00:28:00,890 --> 00:28:02,100
Send me the coordinates.

360
00:28:02,546 --> 00:28:03,700
I’m on my way.

361
00:29:18,560 --> 00:29:19,850
FORENSIC

362
00:29:22,955 --> 00:29:24,198
They want us to find the body.

363
00:29:24,859 --> 00:29:26,351
This is set up for us.

364
00:30:23,023 --> 00:30:25,502
I should finally really
take away that spare keycard.

365
00:30:28,950 --> 00:30:31,696
I mean, it was you
who bought the room next to mine.

366
00:30:32,630 --> 00:30:34,299
How come you came home in the morning?

367
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:35,903
Where’s my Kaye’s autograph?

368
00:30:37,850 --> 00:30:38,720
I didn’t get it.

369
00:30:40,050 --> 00:30:40,802
What?

370
00:30:42,918 --> 00:30:43,697
Here.

371
00:30:44,290 --> 00:30:45,000
Oh!

372
00:30:45,644 --> 00:30:46,897
On your jacket?

373
00:30:47,108 --> 00:30:48,900
How did you get the VIP treatment?

374
00:30:48,994 --> 00:30:50,404
That’s a big autograph, too!

375
00:30:51,487 --> 00:30:52,354
How’d you do that?

376
00:30:52,891 --> 00:30:53,700
What the heck?

377
00:30:54,149 --> 00:30:54,899
Hold on.

378
00:30:55,149 --> 00:30:56,402
13500.

379
00:30:56,605 --> 00:30:57,330
Pay up.

380
00:30:57,602 --> 00:30:59,500
That’s too much! You must be joking.

381
00:30:59,630 --> 00:31:00,650
That’s overpriced.

382
00:31:01,075 --> 00:31:01,977
You want it or not?

383
00:31:02,854 --> 00:31:03,890
I’m your sister!

384
00:31:04,650 --> 00:31:06,601
I’m throwing it
in the washing machine, then.

385
00:31:07,962 --> 00:31:09,499
Hold on, hold on.

386
00:31:11,616 --> 00:31:12,900
I’m kinda broke right now.

387
00:31:12,995 --> 00:31:14,200
Can I pay in installment?

388
00:31:14,834 --> 00:31:15,502
Sure.

389
00:31:15,688 --> 00:31:16,690
Deal. Got it.

390
00:31:17,641 --> 00:31:18,802
Okay, okay.

391
00:31:19,502 --> 00:31:20,296
Okay.

392
00:31:21,376 --> 00:31:22,200
Where’s my boxset?

393
00:31:22,225 --> 00:31:23,302
5000.

394
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:25,598
I’m kidding.

395
00:31:25,930 --> 00:31:26,694
Here.

396
00:31:27,924 --> 00:31:29,002
Thank you.

397
00:31:30,764 --> 00:31:31,702
This is insane!

398
00:31:53,860 --> 00:31:55,050
That’s sick.

399
00:31:55,651 --> 00:31:56,299
Hey.

400
00:31:58,630 --> 00:32:00,200
You’re too young to be seeing these.

401
00:32:00,862 --> 00:32:02,002
I just want a peek.

402
00:32:02,928 --> 00:32:06,995
Those corpses look exactly like
a manga I read.

403
00:32:09,614 --> 00:32:10,697
Manga?

404
00:32:10,925 --> 00:32:12,480
I’m gonna give you a mega hit in the head.

405
00:32:13,552 --> 00:32:14,400
Get out.

406
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:15,601
I’m going to bed.

407
00:32:15,850 --> 00:32:16,810
Are you, though?

408
00:32:16,940 --> 00:32:17,977
Yes, I am.

409
00:32:18,007 --> 00:32:18,770
I’m going to sleep.

410
00:32:18,794 --> 00:32:19,358
Get out.

411
00:32:19,377 --> 00:32:20,497
Liar.

412
00:32:21,290 --> 00:32:22,845
Do you want me to take that jacket back?

413
00:32:23,133 --> 00:32:23,980
Don’t you dare!

414
00:32:51,075 --> 00:32:51,800
Alright.

415
00:32:53,284 --> 00:32:54,405
Beautiful.

416
00:33:00,066 --> 00:33:01,699
Smells awful, though.

417
00:33:02,287 --> 00:33:03,354
I should frame this.

418
00:33:10,023 --> 00:33:11,597
Frames near me.

419
00:33:18,380 --> 00:33:19,100
Let me see.

420
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:19,897
Hey!

421
00:33:24,380 --> 00:33:25,397
Nekros!

422
00:33:53,057 --> 00:33:54,699
The next candidate, please.

423
00:33:57,762 --> 00:33:58,597
Oh, clumsy me.

424
00:34:10,189 --> 00:34:11,240
Are you nervous?

425
00:34:12,450 --> 00:34:13,103
Yeah.

426
00:34:13,914 --> 00:34:14,899
Don’t rush.

427
00:34:15,946 --> 00:34:17,099
Take a deep breath.

428
00:34:24,111 --> 00:34:25,002
Thank you.

429
00:34:26,810 --> 00:34:27,802
I’m Prim.

430
00:34:28,570 --> 00:34:29,595
I’m Praew.

431
00:34:31,362 --> 00:34:32,903
Be confident.

432
00:34:33,411 --> 00:34:35,602
Just say what’s on your mind
in the interview.

433
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:39,700
Do your best.

434
00:34:40,808 --> 00:34:41,801
Smile more.

435
00:34:43,484 --> 00:34:44,201
Good job.

436
00:34:45,151 --> 00:34:45,980
Thanks.

437
00:34:51,980 --> 00:34:53,600
Praewphat Traikanawut.

438
00:34:59,383 --> 00:35:00,601
That’s a famous surname.

439
00:35:01,700 --> 00:35:03,210
But this is Thun Insight.

440
00:35:03,731 --> 00:35:04,902
I don’t care about that.

441
00:35:05,598 --> 00:35:07,201
We only care about your brain,

442
00:35:07,536 --> 00:35:09,099
not your surname.

443
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:13,201
I remember you, you know?

444
00:35:13,509 --> 00:35:16,480
From last year at my lecture.

445
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:19,697
An eleventh grader who gave me an answer…

446
00:35:20,134 --> 00:35:23,000
on media ethics
and public moral satisfaction.

447
00:35:24,157 --> 00:35:25,000
You know,

448
00:35:25,788 --> 00:35:27,296
you have good ideas.

449
00:35:29,810 --> 00:35:31,974
That’s why you’re the candidate
for this internship.

450
00:35:32,591 --> 00:35:33,970
You remember?

451
00:35:34,231 --> 00:35:34,902
Yeah.

452
00:35:35,367 --> 00:35:36,299
Of course.

453
00:35:37,080 --> 00:35:38,500
But it’s too bad.

454
00:35:38,770 --> 00:35:41,183
You looked more confident that day.

455
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:49,167
I’ll give you one minute.

456
00:35:49,986 --> 00:35:51,601
You can say whatever you want.

457
00:35:52,010 --> 00:35:53,601
If you don’t have anything to say,

458
00:35:53,980 --> 00:35:55,502
the door’s that way.

459
00:36:02,797 --> 00:36:03,598
The…

460
00:36:05,750 --> 00:36:09,980
The serial killer case on TV right now,

461
00:36:10,100 --> 00:36:11,503
I think it’s just like…

462
00:36:11,690 --> 00:36:14,120
this one underground webtoon
I’ve read before.

463
00:36:15,447 --> 00:36:16,130
What’s it called?

464
00:36:16,392 --> 00:36:17,598
Nekros.

465
00:36:37,528 --> 00:36:38,502
How was it?

466
00:36:41,071 --> 00:36:42,401
Thun liked it!

467
00:36:43,023 --> 00:36:43,802
He did?

468
00:36:44,034 --> 00:36:46,400
Thun said my ideas are cool!

469
00:36:48,477 --> 00:36:49,801
Congratulations.

470
00:36:50,380 --> 00:36:52,010
I told you you got this.

471
00:36:52,365 --> 00:36:53,500
Two thumbs up!

472
00:36:57,494 --> 00:36:58,365
Inspector.

473
00:37:00,340 --> 00:37:01,051
Yeah?

474
00:37:02,330 --> 00:37:04,111
Here’s the list
of all psychiatric patients

475
00:37:04,130 --> 00:37:05,650
with a history of violence.

476
00:37:07,180 --> 00:37:10,802
Most of them are currently imprisoned,
otherwise, they have alibis.

477
00:37:13,880 --> 00:37:16,801
As for the people with personal grudges,
no one is especially suspicious.

478
00:37:25,940 --> 00:37:27,801
There has to be a connection.

479
00:37:31,481 --> 00:37:34,103
The two victims have nothing in common.

480
00:37:35,395 --> 00:37:36,797
They work in different businesses.

481
00:37:37,770 --> 00:37:39,103
They run in different circles.

482
00:37:41,050 --> 00:37:42,998
What’s the criteria here?

483
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:50,960
(Breaking news regarding
the serial killer case)

484
00:37:50,986 --> 00:37:53,496
(in which the police
are still searching for the murderer.)

485
00:37:53,660 --> 00:37:56,730
(Our research found that this murderer)

486
00:37:56,958 --> 00:38:00,650
(imitates the murders
in an underground manga called Nekros.)

487
00:38:00,789 --> 00:38:03,890
(Whether or not that is accurate,
I implore you to decide for yourself.)

488
00:38:03,920 --> 00:38:07,800
MURDER CASES IMITATE MANGA

489
00:38:07,990 --> 00:38:08,899
Crap.

490
00:38:09,660 --> 00:38:10,703
It’s the same.

491
00:38:11,580 --> 00:38:14,300
(It begs the questions:
who writes this manga,)

492
00:38:14,405 --> 00:38:17,980
(and how did they know
these murders would happen.)

493
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:20,400
(That is what we need to find answers for.)

494
00:38:22,380 --> 00:38:23,097
Nop.

495
00:38:23,230 --> 00:38:23,896
Yes?

496
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:24,930
Get in touch with Cyber

497
00:38:25,210 --> 00:38:27,902
and find whatever there is to find
about this comic.

498
00:38:28,450 --> 00:38:29,294
Yes, sir.

499
00:38:33,918 --> 00:38:37,604
(If the murders are based off
the underground manga Nekros,)

500
00:38:37,899 --> 00:38:42,099
(that means the police’s investigation
might be leading the wrong way.)

501
00:38:42,380 --> 00:38:43,600
(The murderer chose their victims)

502
00:38:43,630 --> 00:38:46,656
(and was inspired by the manga,
panel-by-panel.)

503
00:38:46,690 --> 00:38:50,896
(It wouldn’t be an overstatement to say
Nekros is the murderer’s Bible.)

504
00:40:06,140 --> 00:40:07,503
I guess you saw the news.

505
00:40:08,300 --> 00:40:09,500
I did.

506
00:40:11,122 --> 00:40:12,456
You wouldn't listen to me.

507
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:15,170
I tried to tell you,
but I bet you think I was being silly.

508
00:40:15,342 --> 00:40:15,967
See?

509
00:40:15,986 --> 00:40:17,980
I got my internship because of this.

510
00:40:18,371 --> 00:40:19,202
You know why?

511
00:40:19,380 --> 00:40:21,650
Because Thun actually listens to me,
unlike you.

512
00:40:23,275 --> 00:40:24,496
Alright, alright.

513
00:40:25,299 --> 00:40:26,226
It was my fault.

514
00:40:26,260 --> 00:40:27,299
I’m sorry.

515
00:40:28,657 --> 00:40:33,197
But I really need to know more
about this manga right now.

516
00:40:33,893 --> 00:40:35,010
Can you send it to me?

517
00:40:35,725 --> 00:40:36,640
I don’t have it.

518
00:40:38,590 --> 00:40:39,979
Or I do?

519
00:40:40,802 --> 00:40:41,496
Hey.

520
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:45,000
I mean, if you give me
that jacket for free,

521
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:46,280
I might have something for you.

522
00:40:50,510 --> 00:40:51,395
Alright, alright.

523
00:40:51,568 --> 00:40:52,200
Fine.

524
00:40:52,350 --> 00:40:53,200
Here it is.

525
00:40:53,845 --> 00:40:56,201
The author’s been
on hiatus for years, though.

526
00:40:56,549 --> 00:40:58,130
I didn’t download every chapter,
by the way.

527
00:40:59,693 --> 00:41:00,650
Who’s the artist?

528
00:41:01,026 --> 00:41:02,700
His pen name is Mr. Kill.

529
00:41:02,853 --> 00:41:05,617
He’s pretty much a niche artist,
well known among underground audiences.

530
00:41:05,648 --> 00:41:07,502
Dark fantasy, you know.

531
00:41:08,447 --> 00:41:09,610
You know who he really is?

532
00:41:09,896 --> 00:41:11,402
No. No one does.

533
00:41:11,429 --> 00:41:12,801
He’s never revealed himself.

534
00:41:13,365 --> 00:41:14,650
But if you want to know,

535
00:41:15,127 --> 00:41:17,103
you should try asking around
publishing houses.

536
00:41:17,352 --> 00:41:18,899
His art style is unique.

537
00:41:19,150 --> 00:41:21,097
I bet some editors have seen this before.

538
00:41:55,250 --> 00:41:56,300
This is the last one.

539
00:41:57,093 --> 00:41:59,702
If there’s still no lead,
we gotta find another way.

540
00:42:00,540 --> 00:42:01,297
Yes, sir.

541
00:42:01,517 --> 00:42:02,198
Let’s go.

542
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:13,000
Oh, Mr. Kaye.

543
00:42:14,472 --> 00:42:15,013
Uh…

544
00:42:15,037 --> 00:42:16,300
What a small world.

545
00:42:16,682 --> 00:42:17,256
You…

546
00:42:17,281 --> 00:42:18,570
The hero from that day.

547
00:42:18,764 --> 00:42:20,810
It’s Phat. Please call me Phat.

548
00:42:21,533 --> 00:42:22,250
Okay.

549
00:42:22,515 --> 00:42:24,602
Do you work here?

550
00:42:26,416 --> 00:42:27,100
Yes.

551
00:42:27,442 --> 00:42:29,702
I’m a manga artist under this company.

552
00:42:30,346 --> 00:42:33,402
What are you doing here today, Mr. Phat?

553
00:42:34,167 --> 00:42:36,303
I’m here to meet someone.

554
00:42:36,845 --> 00:42:37,697
I see.

555
00:42:42,254 --> 00:42:43,900
But it’s good to see you.

556
00:42:51,579 --> 00:42:54,040
You know, that jacket
you signed the other day.

557
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:56,801
My sister was practically screaming for it.

558
00:42:57,970 --> 00:42:59,897
Not to mention the profit I got out of it.

559
00:43:00,964 --> 00:43:02,897
It’s all thanks to you.

560
00:43:04,150 --> 00:43:05,299
Thank you.

561
00:43:06,120 --> 00:43:11,730
I’m glad my autograph
is at least profitable.

562
00:43:11,943 --> 00:43:16,500
I thought you’d get mad at me
for ruining your jacket.

563
00:43:17,210 --> 00:43:18,248
Of course not.

564
00:43:19,560 --> 00:43:22,900
Seeing you smile makes it all worth it.

565
00:43:43,880 --> 00:43:44,595
Please.

566
00:43:44,860 --> 00:43:45,699
Thank you.

567
00:43:52,068 --> 00:43:53,982
Inspector, the editor’s in today.

568
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:04,099
We might find something here, after all.

569
00:44:43,710 --> 00:44:44,600
Excuse me.

570
00:44:44,960 --> 00:44:45,700
Yes?

571
00:44:45,971 --> 00:44:47,600
We’re here to see Editor Vichai.

572
00:44:49,402 --> 00:44:50,503
Is something the matter?

573
00:44:51,213 --> 00:44:53,299
We’re looking for the artist
behind this manga.

574
00:44:53,740 --> 00:44:54,800
Can I see?

575
00:45:04,546 --> 00:45:05,502
This way, please.

576
00:45:05,760 --> 00:45:06,601
Yes.

577
00:45:09,820 --> 00:45:11,330
-Editor.
-Oh, hey, Kaye.

578
00:45:13,860 --> 00:45:15,800
These people are here
to see an artist of ours.

579
00:45:17,630 --> 00:45:18,349
Oh?

580
00:46:05,490 --> 00:46:07,103
Where are you rushing off to, Mr. Kaye?

581
00:46:40,880 --> 00:46:43,001
Well, then, Mr. Kaye…

582
00:46:43,471 --> 00:46:44,299
This way, please.

583
00:47:06,063 --> 00:47:06,896
Yes, Nop?

584
00:47:07,808 --> 00:47:08,700
Who’s missing?

585
00:47:10,071 --> 00:47:11,000
How long?

586
00:47:12,210 --> 00:47:13,297
I’m on my way.

587
00:47:36,197 --> 00:47:37,499
He even drew a heart, huh?

588
00:47:50,365 --> 00:47:51,100
Hey.

589
00:47:51,842 --> 00:47:53,998
Do you recognize this artist?

590
00:47:56,105 --> 00:47:57,127
Excuse me.

591
00:47:57,190 --> 00:48:01,983
Other people wouldn’t panic like that
even when he’s being cornered.

592
00:48:02,602 --> 00:48:04,697
Only someone with a secret does.

593
00:48:05,330 --> 00:48:06,210
Mr. Kaye.

594
00:48:06,765 --> 00:48:08,602
The man whose autograph is on your jacket.

595
00:48:08,927 --> 00:48:11,982
You need to stay
where I can see you. 24/7.

596
00:48:12,228 --> 00:48:14,370
You go where I go. Eat where I eat.

597
00:48:14,630 --> 00:48:15,502
Sleep where I sleep.

598
00:48:17,280 --> 00:48:18,302
Are you for real?

